    • Method Detail

      • resetVersions

        public ModuleDependencyVersions resetVersions()
        Relevant for needsUpdate(SModule) and update(SModule), by default update methods don't change recorded version of a dependency that's not among actual module dependencies. Change behavior to record only actual dependencies and their versions with this method. The flag is quite dubious, and is not easy to explain use cases. Primarily employed by Migration code and likely shall be ignored by others.

      • needsUpdate

        public boolean needsUpdate​(@NotNull
                           SModule module)
        Tells if version of module dependencies are not in accordance with expectations and it's worth to update(SModule) them. Needs read access to a repository

      • update

        public void update​(@NotNull
                   SModule module)
        Bring versions of module dependencies to reflect actual state of language/module repository Needs write access to a module repository in case module has been attached to one. Needs at least read access to a repository we resolve dependencies with.

      • dependenciesPresent

        public boolean dependenciesPresent​(SModule module)
        Tells if supplied language/module repository contain all necessary dependencies of the module. Unlike needsUpdate(SModule), this method doesn't check language/module versions, just the fact they could be discovered.
